[30;1m63 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m64 | [0m[35mGitPython is not suited for long-running processes (like daemons) as it tends to[0m
[30;1m65 | [0m[35mleak system resources. It was written in a time where destructors (as implemented[0m
[30;1m66 | [0m[35min the `__del__` method) still ran deterministically.[0m
[30;1m67 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m68 | [0m[35mIn case you still want to use it in such a context, you will want to search the[0m

[30;1m166 | [0m[35m#### Leakage of System Resources[0m
[30;1m167 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m168 | [0m[35mGitPython is not suited for long-running processes (like daemons) as it tends to[0m
[30;1m169 | [0m[35mleak system resources. It was written in a time where destructors (as implemented[0m
[30;1m170 | [0m[35min the `__del__` method) still ran deterministically.[0m
[30;1m171 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m172 | [0m[35mIn case you still want to use it in such a context, you will want to search the[0m

[30;1m469 | [0m[35mstart, at least in a codebase as old as GitPython, which totally doesn't handle encodings correctly [0m

[30;1m472 | [0m[35mtrivial, but at least `Rust` makes clear what has to be done at compile time, allowing to write soft[0m
